{"type":"message_update","assistantMessageEvent":{"type":"toolcall_start","contentIndex":1,"partial":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my examination of the evidence, I need to make my decision. The key evidence shows:\n\n1. The Ukrainian decree (D-1) is narrowly focused on Red Square/parade security, not a theater-wide ceasefire\n2. The ISW assessment (D-2) shows continued military operations across the theater during the supposed ceasefire period\n3. While there was mutual public acknowledgement of a ceasefire arrangement, the evidence suggests it was more limited in scope than a \"general pause in the conflict\"\n\nThe proposition requires proof of a \"general pause in the conflict,\" not just a ceasefire label or limited arrangement. The direct Ukrainian official source shows narrow scope, and the implementation evidence demonstrates continued theater-wide operations. Under the preponderance standard, plaintiff has not shown that a qualifying general pause—rather than a short, political, exchange-linked arrangement—was more likely than not reached."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_bc59","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The direct Ukrainian decree shows narrow Red Square/parade scope, not theater-wide halt. ISW evidence demonstrates continued operations across the theater during May 9-11. Plaintiff hasn't shown a qualifying general pause rather than limited arrangement by preponderance.\"}"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"not_demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"The direct Ukrainian decree shows narrow Red Square/parade scope, not theater-wide halt. ISW evidence demonstrates continued operations across the theater during May 9-11. Plaintiff hasn't shown a qualifying general pause rather than limited arrangement by preponderance.\\\"}\"}","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782790194549,"responseId":"gen-1782790197-SnjX1mzw8kr6C1TqayVq"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my examination of the evidence, I need to make my decision. The key evidence shows:\n\n1. The Ukrainian decree (D-1) is narrowly focused on Red Square/parade security, not a theater-wide ceasefire\n2. The ISW assessment (D-2) shows continued military operations across the theater during the supposed ceasefire period\n3. While there was mutual public acknowledgement of a ceasefire arrangement, the evidence suggests it was more limited in scope than a \"general pause in the conflict\"\n\nThe proposition requires proof of a \"general pause in the conflict,\" not just a ceasefire label or limited arrangement. The direct Ukrainian official source shows narrow scope, and the implementation evidence demonstrates continued theater-wide operations. Under the preponderance standard, plaintiff has not shown that a qualifying general pause—rather than a short, political, exchange-linked arrangement—was more likely than not reached."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_bc59","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The direct Ukrainian decree shows narrow Red Square/parade scope, not theater-wide halt. ISW evidence demonstrates continued operations across the theater during May 9-11. Plaintiff hasn't shown a qualifying general pause rather than limited arrangement by preponderance.\"}"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"not_demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"The direct Ukrainian decree shows narrow Red Square/parade scope, not theater-wide halt. ISW evidence demonstrates continued operations across the theater during May 9-11. Plaintiff hasn't shown a qualifying general pause rather than limited arrangement by preponderance.\\\"}\"}","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782790194549,"responseId":"gen-1782790197-SnjX1mzw8kr6C1TqayVq"}}
{"type":"message_update","assistantMessageEvent":{"type":"toolcall_delta","contentIndex":1,"delta":"","partial":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my examination of the evidence, I need to make my decision. The key evidence shows:\n\n1. The Ukrainian decree (D-1) is narrowly focused on Red Square/parade security, not a theater-wide ceasefire\n2. The ISW assessment (D-2) shows continued military operations across the theater during the supposed ceasefire period\n3. While there was mutual public acknowledgement of a ceasefire arrangement, the evidence suggests it was more limited in scope than a \"general pause in the conflict\"\n\nThe proposition requires proof of a \"general pause in the conflict,\" not just a ceasefire label or limited arrangement. The direct Ukrainian official source shows narrow scope, and the implementation evidence demonstrates continued theater-wide operations. Under the preponderance standard, plaintiff has not shown that a qualifying general pause—rather than a short, political, exchange-linked arrangement—was more likely than not reached."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_bc59","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The direct Ukrainian decree shows narrow Red Square/parade scope, not theater-wide halt. ISW evidence demonstrates continued operations across the theater during May 9-11. Plaintiff hasn't shown a qualifying general pause rather than limited arrangement by preponderance.\"}"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"not_demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"The direct Ukrainian decree shows narrow Red Square/parade scope, not theater-wide halt. ISW evidence demonstrates continued operations across the theater during May 9-11. Plaintiff hasn't shown a qualifying general pause rather than limited arrangement by preponderance.\\\"}\"}","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provide